Description: Body sherd of East Greek grey ware large pottery vessel, possibly a krater or dinos; dark grey fabric with mica and limestone inclusions; very worn dark slip and inscription with added red paint on exterior.
Curator's comments: Red paint applied to the inscription can also be observed in a few other cases of grey ware at Naukratis. Sherd joins British Museum 1965, 0930.404, and probably from same vase as 1888,0601.623, which is the only other bucchero pot with a two-line inscription.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.015)
